  "prompt": "What is the minimum marks needed to get mechanical branch in BITS Pilani?",
  "response": "The minimum marks required to secure admission to the Mechanical Engineering branch at BITS Pilani can vary each year depending on factors like the difficulty level of the BITSAT exam, the number of applicants, and the number of available seats. Generally, candidates need to score quite high in the BITSAT to have a good chance of getting into prestigious branches like Mechanical Engineering at any of the BITS campuses. \n\nFor a more accurate and updated cutoff score, I recommend checking the official BITS Pilani website or contacting their admissions office. Past trends often indicate cutoff scores in the range of 300 to 350 out of 450 for Mechanical Engineering, but these can fluctuate.",
